cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CC

The paper deals with improving the quality of query translation in cross-language information retrieval, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely categories. The proposed method involves learning low-dimensional vectors of words and finding a query-dependent transformation matrix, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL). Hence, cs.LG and cs.AI are also likely categories. Finally, the paper involves experiments and evaluations, which may fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
